  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If we view the blockchain as a public utility, would it not make sense that we should put in some kind of incentive for developers to \"Clean up\" once their contract has executed its function. This would reduce the load on the state, and help keep the protocol decentralized. Where this incentive would come from, I'm not certain, but I think it's definitely something that ought to be thought about. Any and all ideas I would love to have the discussion about. \n",
